  abstract = {This paper examines the potential of combining Internet of Things (IoT) and Distributed Ledger Technology (DLT) to enable digital circular economy practices for electronic equipment. We develop a framework that leverages these technologies to track electronic products throughout their lifecycle, collecting data from embedded sensors and storing it immutably on blockchain systems. Using case studies of various electronic equipment, we evaluate how this technological combination can enhance transparency and traceability in supply chains. Our findings demonstrate that IoT-DLT integration can significantly improve product lifecycle management by providing reliable information for repair, reuse, and recycling decisions, thereby extending product lifespans and reducing electronic waste while creating new business opportunities within circular economy models.},
