  abstract = {This paper details a service-learning approach to computer reuse through an educational program that simultaneously develops students' technical skills and social consciousness. We implemented our program in an academic setting, where students refurbished and repurposed obsolete computers while gaining practical experience in hardware maintenance. Using qualitative and quantitative assessments of both the educational outcomes and the environmental impact, we evaluated the effectiveness of combining service learning with electronic waste reduction. Our findings indicate that the program successfully extended the useful life of computing equipment while enhancing students' technical capabilities and awareness of sustainability issues, demonstrating an effective educational model that addresses electronic waste challenges while providing valuable community service.},
